msgstr "The amount of data a stream uses per second, usually in megabits per second (Mb/s). For a given codec, more bitrate means better picture quality and more bandwidth used. Encoders trade bitrate against quality and resolution; a multiview canvas is typically encoded at one fixed bitrate per rendition."

